Israeli Stocks: Discount Bank, Cellcom, Makhteshim-Agan

-- B y   S h a r o n   W r o b e l
-- 
2011-08-08T14:14:24Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-08-08/israeli-stocks-discount-bank-cellcom-makhteshim-agan.html
Israel ’s TA-25 Index rose for the
first time in almost two weeks, gaining 1.5 percent to 1,090.39
at the 4:30 p.m. close in  Tel Aviv . Investors traded about 2.28
billion shekels ($640 million) in shares and convertible
securities today, according to Tel Aviv Stock Exchange data.  The following stocks rose or fell today. Symbols are in
parentheses. Local markets will be closed tomorrow for a public
fast.  Cellcom Israel Ltd. (CEL)   slumped to the lowest level
since December 2008, retreating 2.4 percent to 79.56 shekels.
The country’s largest mobile phone operator reported second-
quarter net income that fell to 244 million shekels from 326
million shekels a year earlier.  Israel Discount Bank Ltd. (DSCT)   soared the most since
June 13, increasing 4.7 percent to 5.697 shekels. UBS AG added
the country’s third-largest lender to its Pan-European Top 20
small/midcaps Key Calls list.  Makhteshim-Agan Industries Ltd. (MAIN)   advanced 2.6
percent to 19.04 shekels, the biggest gain since June 13. The
agrochemicals maker said second-quarter net income almost
quadrupled to $45.4 million from $12.4 million a year earlier.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Sharon Wrobel in Tel Aviv at 
 swrobel4@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
